Description



Product Description
Autograph Signature of Jackson, Andrew (7th President) on Partly printed check, accomplished in his own hand and signed.  Nashville:  28 May 1828.  Approx. 8” x 2-½”.
The candidate and future president writes a check for $20.00 to himself, ironically from the “Cashier of the Office of the Bank of the United States at Nashville”.
Jackson waged war against the Second Bank of the United States, unsuccessfully keeping the Bank with its “attendant evils and corruptions” out of his city the previous year, but ultimately destroying the Bank by the end of his presidency.
Oblong;  ½” tear on left edge, not effecting text; four vertical folds; lt. browning; else v.g.; w/ 1861 engraving of “Old Hickory”; 5-½” x  7-½” (sight), 8-¼” x 10-¾” (overall); lt. fox. edges, else v..g.



