Andrew Jackson, The People’s President
Tennessee lawyer, judge, soldier, planter, and politician, Andrew Jackson was the most beloved military hero of his day and one of the most influential presidents in American history.
This compelling book highlights the events of Andrew Jackson’s life – from his meager beginnings to his election as 7th president of the United States. With dozens of rare artifacts and captivating archival images, the book spotlights and honors the 7th President’s life and legacy.


